{"title":"Vittoria Launches New Terreno Range, Gravel Terrain Score, & Gravel Air-Liner","link":"https://bikerumor.com/vittoria-terreno-range-terrain-score-gravel-air-liner/","date":1744292972000,"content":"<p><img src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Vittoria-gravel-updates-tires--1536x1152.webp\" width=\"1536\" height=\"1152\" alt=\"Vittoria gravel updates tires\" /></p>\n<p>Vittoria is coming in hot to the 2025 Sea Otter Classic. Starting from the ground up, adding a clear focus on helping riders make smarter tire choices for a better gravel experience. The Italian Tire Titan released a trio of updates that signal a more refined, rider-first approach to gravel tech.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Vittoria-gravel-updates--scaled.webp\"><img width=\"2560\" height=\"1920\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Vittoria-gravel-updates--scaled.webp\" alt=\"Vittoria gravel updates\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Vittoria-gravel-updates--scaled.webp 2560w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Vittoria-gravel-updates--297x223.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Vittoria-gravel-updates--1536x1152.webp 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Vittoria-gravel-updates--120x90.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Vittoria-gravel-updates--768x576.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Vittoria-gravel-updates--2048x1536.webp 2048w\" /></a><figcaption>(Photos: Vittoria)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3><strong>Terrain Score: Gravel Tire Decision-Making Tool </strong></h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The first update is the all-new Gravel Terrain Score, a scale designed to demystify tire selection. Riders tackling everything from buttery hardpack to sloppy post-thunderstorm singletrack can find clear tire tread guidance. Born from the data-heavy <a href=\"https://vittoria.com/blogs/magazine/tagged/tech\">Vittoria White Paper #4</a> and refined with input from pro athletes. The Terrain Score system breaks riding surfaces into five super-categories: Hardpack, Fine Loose, Mixed, Coarse Loose, and Mud.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Vittoria-gravel-updates-Gravel-Terriain-score-.png\"><img width=\"2462\" height=\"1532\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Vittoria-gravel-updates-Gravel-Terriain-score-.png\" alt=\"Vittoria gravel updates Gravel Terriain score\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Vittoria-gravel-updates-Gravel-Terriain-score-.png 2462w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Vittoria-gravel-updates-Gravel-Terriain-score--297x185.png 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Vittoria-gravel-updates-Gravel-Terriain-score--1536x956.png 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Vittoria-gravel-updates-Gravel-Terriain-score--120x75.png 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Vittoria-gravel-updates-Gravel-Terriain-score--768x478.png 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Vittoria-gravel-updates-Gravel-Terriain-score--2048x1274.png 2048w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Think of it as a matchmaking tool for you and your tires. Each category is scored from 0 (pavement territory) to 100 (cue the MTB playlist), giving riders an intuitive roadmap to the best tire for the job.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><em>“Riders can now simply look at the terrain they’ll face and trace down to the tire that fits,” says Stijn Vriends, Vittoria’s Chairman &amp; CEO. “It’s about simplifying choices so gravel cyclists spend less time guessing and more time riding.”</em></p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Vittoria-gravel-updates-tire--scaled.webp\"><img width=\"2560\" height=\"1707\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Vittoria-gravel-updates-tire--scaled.webp\" alt=\"Vittoria gravel updates tire\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Vittoria-gravel-updates-tire--scaled.webp 2560w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Vittoria-gravel-updates-tire--297x198.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Vittoria-gravel-updates-tire--1536x1024.webp 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Vittoria-gravel-updates-tire--120x80.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Vittoria-gravel-updates-tire--768x512.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Vittoria-gravel-updates-tire--2048x1365.webp 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Vittoria-gravel-updates-tire--800x533.webp 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Vittoria-gravel-updates-tire--720x480.webp 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3><strong>New Terrain, New Names: Terreno Range Rebooted</strong></h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Vittoria is also renaming and updating its Endurance Gravel tire lineup to match the Terrain Score. Out with the Terreno naming convention, in with the new Terrain Score-based labels:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Terreno Zero</strong> becomes <strong>T10</strong></li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Terreno Dry</strong> becomes <strong>T30</strong></li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Terreno Mix </strong>becomes <strong>T50</strong></li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Mezcal-style</strong> knobs come in as the <strong>T70</strong></li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Vittoria-gravel-updates-photos--scaled.webp\"><img width=\"2560\" height=\"1920\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Vittoria-gravel-updates-photos--scaled.webp\" alt=\"Vittoria gravel updates photos\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Vittoria-gravel-updates-photos--scaled.webp 2560w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Vittoria-gravel-updates-photos--297x223.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Vittoria-gravel-updates-photos--1536x1152.webp 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Vittoria-gravel-updates-photos--120x90.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Vittoria-gravel-updates-photos--768x576.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Vittoria-gravel-updates-photos--2048x1536.webp 2048w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The T50 Mixed Gravel Endurance tire leads the charge. Slotted perfectly between the T30 and the more aggressive T70, this tire aims to be the go-to for riders who are dabbling in chunky, loose-over-hard terrain but still want a fast-rolling, all-day setup.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Vittoria-gravel-updates-ridley--scaled.webp\"><img width=\"2560\" height=\"1707\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Vittoria-gravel-updates-ridley--scaled.webp\" alt=\"Vittoria gravel updates ridley\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Vittoria-gravel-updates-ridley--scaled.webp 2560w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Vittoria-gravel-updates-ridley--297x198.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Vittoria-gravel-updates-ridley--1536x1024.webp 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Vittoria-gravel-updates-ridley--120x80.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Vittoria-gravel-updates-ridley--768x512.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Vittoria-gravel-updates-ridley--2048x1365.webp 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Vittoria-gravel-updates-ridley--800x533.webp 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Vittoria-gravel-updates-ridley--720x480.webp 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The T50 isn’t just a rebrand. It sports a directional siping texture for more grip in loose corners, plus Vittoria’s reinforced nylon sidewall protection and endurance-focused construction. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Vittoria-gravel-updates-5oT--scaled.webp\"><img width=\"2560\" height=\"1921\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Vittoria-gravel-updates-5oT--scaled.webp\" alt=\"Vittoria gravel updates 5oT\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Vittoria-gravel-updates-5oT--scaled.webp 2560w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Vittoria-gravel-updates-5oT--297x223.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Vittoria-gravel-updates-5oT--1536x1152.webp 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Vittoria-gravel-updates-5oT--120x90.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Vittoria-gravel-updates-5oT--768x576.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Vittoria-gravel-updates-5oT--2048x1536.webp 2048w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Powered by a graphene-based compound, it’s built for the long haul and changing conditions — bike-packing epics, gravel grinders, or whatever your “unmaintained road” route throws at you.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Vittoria-gravel-updates-logo-air-liner-.webp\"><img width=\"1281\" height=\"1920\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Vittoria-gravel-updates-logo-air-liner-.webp\" alt=\"Vittoria gravel updates logo air liner\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Vittoria-gravel-updates-logo-air-liner-.webp 1281w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Vittoria-gravel-updates-logo-air-liner--200x300.webp 200w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Vittoria-gravel-updates-logo-air-liner--80x120.webp 80w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Vittoria-gravel-updates-logo-air-liner--768x1151.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Vittoria-gravel-updates-logo-air-liner--1025x1536.webp 1025w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3><strong>Air-Liner Light Gravel Insert Expands for More Riders</strong></h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Last but not least is the updated Air-Liner. For riders pushing their tires to the edge (literally), Vittoria’s Air-Liner Light Gravel insert now comes in a new 37–40mm. The size complements the existing 42–50mm tire options. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Vittoria-gravel-updates-air-liner-.webp\"><img width=\"1920\" height=\"1280\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Vittoria-gravel-updates-air-liner-.webp\" alt=\"Vittoria gravel updates air liner\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Vittoria-gravel-updates-air-liner-.webp 1920w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Vittoria-gravel-updates-air-liner--297x198.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Vittoria-gravel-updates-air-liner--1536x1024.webp 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Vittoria-gravel-updates-air-liner--120x80.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Vittoria-gravel-updates-air-liner--768x512.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Vittoria-gravel-updates-air-liner--800x533.webp 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Vittoria-gravel-updates-air-liner--720x480.webp 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Born from the DNA of the Air-Liner Light XC and the original Gravel version. The updated insert is designed for more than just flat protection:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Ride Feel:</strong> The insert compresses progressively, smoothing out chatter and reducing fatigue on longer rides.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Burp and Impact Protection:</strong> That same progressive feel helps eliminate burps and protects rims from snake bites.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Run-Flat Capable:</strong> The semi-permeable foam can slowly retain and release air in case of a total flat—and yes, it plays nice with sealant.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p>For racers, adventurers, and anyone flatted five miles from camp. This might be the quiet upgrade that saves your ride (and your sidewalls).</p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://vittoria.com/\">Vittoria.com</a></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/vittoria-terreno-range-terrain-score-gravel-air-liner/\">Vittoria Launches New Terreno Range, Gravel Terrain Score, &amp; Gravel Air-Liner</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Jordan Villella","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"104c97d94b53c6c360b6d35842a8dd79dd0c40de35430f2fc7f0abe94962367c","category":"Cycling"}